## Investigation Complete

**Issue**: #654 - Prod deploy failed on main
**Type**: BUG

### Assessment

| Metric | Value | Reasoning |
|--------|-------|-----------|
| Severity | HIGH | Every push to main fails to deploy; staging and prod are blocked |
| Complexity | LOW | Single-character flag removal, two occurrences, one file |
| Confidence | HIGH | Root cause is mechanically certain |

### Root Cause

`ssh-keyscan -H` was introduced in commit `5854b74` (PR #651). The `-H` flag **hashes** the hostname in `known_hosts`, writing entries like `|1|<salt>|<hash>` instead of the literal IP. The subsequent guard `grep -q "100.120.193.82" ~/.ssh/known_hosts` then always fails because the literal IP is never written. The SSH connection itself was fine (the logs show the host's SSH banner), but the guard exits 1 regardless.

### Fix Applied

Removed `-H` from `ssh-keyscan` at two locations in `.github/workflows/staging-pipeline.yml`:
- Line 42 (deploy-staging job)
- Line 142 (deploy-production job)

